```python
from scipy.optimize import linprog

# Coefficients of the objective function
c = [-7, -10]

# Coefficients of the inequality constraints
A = [[5, 6], [-1, 0.6], [0, -1], [1, 1]]
b = [1500, 0, -50, 100]

# Bounds for variables
x_bounds = (0, None)
y_bounds = (50, None)

# Solve the linear programming problem
res = linprog(c, A_ub=A, b_ub=b, bounds=[x_bounds, y_bounds], method='highs')

# Extract the optimal values
labradors = int(res.x[0])
golden_retrievers = int(res.x[1])
max_newspapers = -int(res.fun)

print("Number of Labradors:", labradors)
print("Number of Golden Retrievers:", golden_retrievers)
print("Maximum Number of Newspapers Delivered:", max_newspapers)
```
